<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
    version="5.0">
    <title>Favour service reuse over object reuse</title>
    <para>
        Service reuse introduces less coupling then object reuse, particularly when decoupling through a services contract.
        Object reuse results in direct coupling to data structures. 
    </para>
    <para>
        In the case of domain entities, these continuously evolve
        in the context of introducing new processes which affect the information to be maintained around these entities and
        in the context of changing business processes.
    </para>
    <para>
        Value objects, on the other hand, are meant to exchange information in the context of particular services. These
        typically evolve with evolving requirements for those services and are unlike 
    </para>
</section>    